CSS Grid Tips

grid-column-start / grid-column-end:
    3
    5
    etc

grid-column: ''/''

grid-row-start: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 etc

grid-area: 1/1/3/6 for ex.

grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 50%)

grid-template-columns: 100px 3em 30% example

fr (Each 'fr' unit allocates one share of the available space)
    example: grid-template-columns: 1fr 5fr

grid-template: (combines both 'grid-template-rows' and 'grid-template-columns')
    example: grid-template: 60% 60% 60% / 200px


You can use centering with flex and grid
    display: flex; * or grid *
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;

place-items: center;


